Bank of Ireland Close to Selling $2 Billion of Assets, Post Says

-- B y   C o l m   H e a t l e y
-- 
2011-09-18T13:23:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-18/bank-of-ireland-close-to-selling-2-billion-of-assets-post-says.html
Bank of Ireland Plc is close to
selling a 1.5 billion-euro ($2.07 billion) portfolio of U.K.
loan assets to Kennedy Wilson, the  Sunday Business Post 
reported, without saying where it got the information.  Bank of Ireland and Kennedy Wilson, which bought a stake in
the lender in July, are close to completing a deal on the
disposal of the loan book, which is secured by U.K. properties,
the Dublin-based paper said today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Colm Heatley in Belfast at 
 cheatley@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net  